Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.44,0:00:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus came to “bear witness to the truth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.44,0:00:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Standing on trial\Nbefore the Roman Governor Pontius Pilate,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.45,0:00:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus boldly stated, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,as recorded at John 18:37:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.33,0:00:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“For this I have come into the world,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.92,0:00:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“that I should bear witness to the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.34,0:00:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“Everyone who is\Non the side of the truth\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.55,0:00:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,listens to my voice.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.47,0:00:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus used his\Nthree-and-a-half year ministry on earth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.60,0:00:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to teach people the truth\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.27,0:00:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jehovah God and His purpose. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.85,0:00:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who were\N“on the side of the truth”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.86,0:00:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,responded favorably\Nand wanted to learn more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.53,0:00:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Others, however,\Nby their response to the good news, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.87,0:00:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,revealed themselves\Nto be enemies of the truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.91,0:01:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As Jesus neared the end\Nof his earthly ministry,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.54,0:01:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,he ‘bore witness\Nto the truth’ during a series\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of dramatic confrontations\Nin the temple. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.18,0:01:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What lessons can we learn\Nfrom the exciting events recorded\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.72,0:01:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in Matthew chapters 21 and 22? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.23,0:01:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As we will see, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.23,0:01:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,these two chapters of Matthew\Nhighlight Jesus’ courage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.11,0:01:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,his masterful teaching ability, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.07,0:01:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and his persistence in bearing \Nthorough witness to the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.95,0:01:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Studying these chapters\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.96,0:01:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will help us to imitate\NJesus’ fine qualities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.21,0:01:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us begin with Matthew chapter 21. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.01,0:01:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Verses 12 to 14 relate how Jesus\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.88,0:01:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,threw out those selling\Nand buying animals in the temple\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.60,0:02:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and overturned the tables\Nof the money changers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.27,0:02:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,These events took place\Non Nisan 10, 33 C.E. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.07,0:02:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.69,0:02:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the chief priests\Ndirectly challenged Jesus’ authority\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.24,0:02:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to disrupt their business. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.45,0:02:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How would he respond? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.91,0:02:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us start the reading at verse 23:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.89,0:07:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In challenging Jesus\Nwith the words in verse 23,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.35,0:07:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“By what authority\Ndo you do these things? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.23,0:07:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And who gave you this authority?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.44,0:07:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the chief priests and elders\Nshowed gross disrespect for Jehovah,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.45,0:07:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,his temple, \Nand his inspired Word of truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.45,0:07:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus boldly countered their challenge\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.87,0:08:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,with a question\Nthat left them speechless,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.21,0:08:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for it exposed them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.21,0:08:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as treacherous and calculating. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.92,0:08:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Before they could recover, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.93,0:08:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus followed up with two illustrations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.06,0:08:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First, he compared the religious leaders\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.52,0:08:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to a rebellious son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.77,0:08:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They had made a promise\Nto do God’s will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.65,0:08:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but had not kept it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.86,0:08:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, Jesus denounced them\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,as wicked caretakers\Nof Jehovah’s “vineyard”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.41,0:08:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,who would be held responsible\Nfor their failure\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.58,0:08:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to cultivate the “fruitage” of faith\Nin God’s Son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.25,0:08:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ illustrations were so masterful\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.46,0:08:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that the chief priests and elders\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.59,0:08:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,unwittingly pronounced judgment\Non themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.06,0:08:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The religious leaders were furious, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.56,0:09:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and they would have tried to kill Jesus\Nbut they feared the crowds. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So they took the indirect approach\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.57,0:09:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and conspired to trap Jesus\Nin his speech. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.86,0:09:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How would Jesus handle\Nthis new challenge? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.45,0:09:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn your attention\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.45,0:09:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to Matthew 22:15-33:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.44,0:12:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was approached first\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.20,0:12:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,by party followers of Herod\Nand disciples of the Pharisees. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.04,0:12:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Although these two groups\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.25,0:12:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,held conflicting\Npolitical and social views, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.83,0:12:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they were united\Nin their hatred for Jesus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.17,0:13:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Flattering words prefaced\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.59,0:13:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a dangerous question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.89,0:13:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Is it lawful to pay head tax\Nto Caesar or not?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Had Jesus answered, \N“Yes, it is lawful,”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.15,0:13:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,he could have enraged the crowd,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.90,0:13:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for many would have felt\Nthat he was condoning the injustices\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.20,0:13:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they suffered at the hands\Nof the Romans. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.41,0:13:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,\Na response such as, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.95,0:13:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is not lawful,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.37,0:13:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,could have sparked a revolt, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.08,0:13:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,resulting in Jesus’ immediate\Narrest for sedition. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.01,0:13:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus did not fall into either trap. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.05,0:13:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, using a coin, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.31,0:13:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,he responded with an object lesson\Nthat amazed his questioners.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.27,0:13:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, the Sadducees,\Nintending to discredit Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.82,0:14:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,proposed a scenario\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.44,0:14:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that they thought would expose\Nbelief in the resurrection\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.28,0:14:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as foolishness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.24,0:14:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In response,\NJesus used flawless reasoning\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.66,0:14:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to highlight Scriptural evidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.67,0:14:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Sadducees had apparently \Nnever considered before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.38,0:14:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They professed to believe the words\Nof Jehovah recorded at Exodus 3:6:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.38,0:14:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am . . . the God of Abraham,\Nthe God of Isaac,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.14,0:14:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the God of Jacob.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.10,0:14:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jehovah spoke those words, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.31,0:14:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Abraham, Isaac,\Nand Jacob had long since died. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.31,0:14:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, Jehovah said “I am” their God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.65,0:14:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not “I was” their God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.53,0:14:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,By speaking\Nof these long-dead patriarchs\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.45,0:14:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as though they were still alive,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.62,0:14:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah showed that his purpose\Nto resurrect his faithful servants\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.96,0:14:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is sure of fulfillment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.09,0:15:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, \NJesus told the Sadducees\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.72,0:15:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that “in the resurrection\Nneither do men marry\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.64,0:15:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,nor are women given in marriage,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.18,0:15:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but they are as angels in heaven.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.98,0:15:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He may have been using\Nthe opportunity\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.60,0:15:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to reveal truths\Nabout the heavenly resurrection\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.69,0:15:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for the benefit of sincere disciples\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.65,0:15:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,who would one day\Nbe in line to receive\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.28,0:15:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,such a resurrection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.12,0:15:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The crowds were astounded\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.95,0:15:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at Jesus’ authoritative teaching\Nfrom the Scriptures.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.50,0:15:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, the Pharisees\Nand Sadducees joined forces\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to test Jesus one last time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.34,0:15:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A scribe from among them,\N“versed in the Law,”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.06,0:15:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,presented a deceptively\Nsimple question, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.85,0:16:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,namely: “Which is\Nthe greatest commandment?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.40,0:16:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In Jesus’ day,\Nthis was a hotly debated question. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.24,0:16:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Would Jesus say something in answer\Nthat would damage his credibility? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.70,0:16:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us listen\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.54,0:16:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to Matthew 22:34-46 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.67,0:16:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn from Jesus’ response. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.88,0:16:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Matthew 22,\Nbeginning with verse 34:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Quoting from God’s Word, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.77,0:18:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus captured the essence\Nof true worship—love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.74,0:19:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mosaic Law consisted\Nof more than 600 individual laws\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.12,0:19:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and regulations,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.87,0:19:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,, yet Jesus\N—without hesitation—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.75,0:19:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,selected the two commandments \Non which “the whole Law hangs.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.75,0:19:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The clear truth of his answer\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.05,0:19:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,cut through human tradition\Nand empty debate.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.80,0:19:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus then turned the tables \Non his opposers with this question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.23,0:19:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If the Christ is to be a “son of David,”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.60,0:19:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then why does David refer to him\Nin the psalms as “my Lord”?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.82,0:19:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,More than a mere riddle, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.82,0:19:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,this question uncovered\Nthe spiritual ignorance\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.58,0:19:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jesus’ enemies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.37,0:19:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Exposed as spiritually blind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.00,0:19:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,his opposers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.00,0:19:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,never dared\Nto question Jesus again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.55,0:19:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we follow Jesus’ example\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.13,0:19:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in bearing witness to the truth?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.68,0:20:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,First, by imitating his courage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.56,0:20:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ courage\Nwas based on faith in God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.94,0:20:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We grow in faith\Nby praying for holy spirit,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.02,0:20:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,by meditating\Non Bible accounts that highlight\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.24,0:20:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the courageous acts of God’s servants, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.61,0:20:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and by allowing what we learn\Nat Christian meetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.83,0:20:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to sink into our hearts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.95,0:20:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing this enables us\Nto build strong faith\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.83,0:20:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on the foundation of truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.34,0:20:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Another way\Nthat we can follow Jesus’ example\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.09,0:20:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in bearing witness to the truth\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.43,0:20:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is by imitating his masterful teaching. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.35,0:20:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We can reach the hearts\Nof sincere listeners with the truth\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.10,0:20:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,by imitating Jesus’ use of questions,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.82,0:20:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,illustrations, and object lessons\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.40,0:21:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as his reasoning\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.78,0:21:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and skillful use of God’s written Word.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.54,0:21:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Third, \Nwe are following Jesus’ example\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.50,0:21:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when we persevere in our efforts\Nto bear thorough witness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.34,0:21:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Never give up in preaching\Nand teaching the good news; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.01,0:21:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,those who reject the truth at first\Nmay respond later. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.60,0:21:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The inspired record\Nin Acts of Apostles tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.31,0:21:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that in time\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.31,0:21:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of Jews\Nbegan paying attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.65,0:21:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to the good news\Nthat had been preached by Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.15,0:21:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,including “a large crowd of priests”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.16,0:21:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and some who had been Pharisees. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.66,0:21:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,These no longer acted in ignorance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.96,0:21:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, they repented\Nand gained Jehovah’s favor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.30,0:22:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether you are facing\Ndirect challenges\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.92,0:22:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or indirect ones,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.01,0:22:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,be determined\Nto bear witness to the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.81,0:22:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jesus did.\N
